In this article, Commerce Secretary Penny Pritzker and Press Secretary Jay Carney discuss President Obama's event in Pennsylvania, where he will be joined by Vice President Biden to talk about skills development and training. Secretary Pritzker explains the importance of engaging with businesses to provide workers with the necessary skills and the need to break down silos between businesses, community colleges, workforce training organizations, universities, and local governments. She also announces two programs aimed at expanding apprenticeship programs and creating industry-recognized credentials. The article also mentions the ongoing situation in Ukraine and the possibility of imposing new sanctions on Russia. Finally, it briefly mentions the sinking of a South Korean ferry and the U.S.'s readiness to provide assistance.